        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 5:06PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 505 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Boca Reservoir. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Prosser Creek Reservoir, Stampede Reservoir, Boca Reservoir,
Glenshire-Devonshire Cdp, Floriston, Hirschdale, Truckee, Ca 89 At
Nevada-Sierra Co Line, Lakeside Campground, Glenshire-Devonshire,
Boca Rest Campground, Logger Campground, Alpine Meadows Campground,
Hobart Mills, Boca Campground, and Truckee-Tahoe Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

If on or near Boca Reservoir, Stampede Reservoir, or Prosser Creek
Reservoir, get out of the water and move indoors or inside a
vehicle. Remember, lightning can strike out to 10 miles from the
parent thunderstorm. If you can hear thunder, you are close enough
to be struck by lightning. Move to safe shelter now! Do not be
caught on the water in a thunderstorm.

Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
this storm passes.</instruction>
